just_use hand.go

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: domain — Hand type + operations (Go side)

Mirror of `elm/src/Game/Hand.elm`. Holds a list
of HandCards; supports add, remove, query, and content-based
lookup.

## Exposed surface

- `type Hand struct { HandCards []HandCard }`
- `EmptyHand() Hand`
- `Hand.IsEmpty() bool`, `Hand.Size() int`
- `Hand.AddCards(cards []Card, state HandCardState) Hand`
- `Hand.RemoveHandCard(target HandCard) Hand` — first-match
  removal by Card identity; silent no-op if not present.
- `Hand.FindByCard(c Card) *HandCard` — content-identity
  lookup; nil if absent.

## Elm divergences

- Elm's `removeHandCard` throws; Go's silently no-ops (same
  total-function contract as the Elm port adopted).
- Naming: Elm uses `Hand.resetState`; Go uses method syntax
  `Hand.ResetState()`. Same semantics — every card back to
  `HandNormal`.

## Turn-logic consumers (present)

- `applyCompleteTurn` in `replay.go` calls
  `ResetState()` on the outgoing player's hand before drawing
  new cards. The "no turn logic on Go side yet" caveat was
  true pre-bcaea72 (2026-04-18); turn logic is now fully
  ported.

## Pointers

- Used by `replay.go` — `State.Hands []Hand` plus the
  `ResetState` call in `applyCompleteTurn`.
- Used by `dealer.go` — `OpeningHand()` returns a Hand.
